I don't mean those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who speak during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it has no meaning.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon may occur occasionally (once in a lifetime, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child cannot remember anything.
There is no single reason to cause this appearance.
Relationships with other manifestations in sleep are often sought, such as nightmares, panic fear at night, Enuresis noctura (bed wetting at night), speaking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stress situations or overburden.
In any case, that's a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that one speaks calmly in individual words, whispers or it can be quite the opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and to consult a specialist to check whether there is a problem that causes fear and thus results.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, be it, it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is carry out a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to excite the child before sleeping.
So, choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are terrible and a little too wild.
For the nervous children who are recommended to relax, relaxation methods can be used to help them to get some inner peace.
This helps the child to sleep calmly.
Once speaking occurs in sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember, it's harmless to the child, and the next day it won't remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will tear it out of your sleep.
Although the child speaks, it sleeps, so it rests.
Remember, when it appears frightened after a pair of appearances, it is recommended to consult or find out what reason the child has for fear.
When they understand what it says (which is not so common), the child does not put pressure on to conduct an interrogation and get more information out.
So you will not be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child sleeps, it is unconscious and cannot think about it.
Besides, you'll hear what it says, but you won't know what it dreams and why it says that, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Maybe, don't tell the kid that you hear it at night and know his secrets.
Not even as a joke.
This causes a lot of fear.
So, don't worry, it's nothing bad, that's a moment that only takes a few minutes.
