The consumer goods sectors recorded a price increase of 6.8 percent, while the fixed goods sector recorded a price reduction of 1.4 percent.
Industrial export prices, measured in Forint, rose by 1.1 percent in August compared to the previous month, but fell by 3.9 percent year-on-year.
