All in all, there is no more breakfast during working hours; no more coffee or croissant.
Brunettas advises with a smile: "A good cappuccino at 7 o'clock works wonders".
During a meeting of the General Committee of Public Administration (Scuola Superiore della Pubblica Amministrazione)
of Rome, the Minister announces that "in three months the absences of officials have been reduced to 50%, i.e. 60.000 people per year are more present at work".
He added that it was necessary to strengthen the efficiency of the Italian public administration.
According to the Minister, "their wage dynamics have been twice as large as the private sector in the last 8-10 years and well above the inflation rate".
In the meantime, thousands of officials have joined forces to counter the Brunetta decree in the context of the appeal supported by Codacons.
"While the Minister of the Public Service is showing up with figures about lower absenteeism at work - according to the Consumer Centre - the people of the 'active lazy' are growing continuously.
